<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="303" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,424,1242]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,323,496,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2005" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2005" box="[600,859,497,521]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Belisana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarika">
<emphasis box="[600,704,497,521]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">B. sarika</emphasis>
Huber, 
<number box="[800,859,497,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by details of pedipalpal morphology (
<figureCitation box="[309,381,533,557]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[199,1384,195,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[199,1386,195,1940]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Belisana tauricornis Thorell, 1898, based on male syntype. A – B. Pedipalpus (A, prolateral view; B, retrolateral view); C – D. Distal part of procursus (C, prolateral view; D, retrolateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216178/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
Figs 
<number box="[372,381,533,557]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A–D and 
<number box="[509,524,533,557]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="2.0">2</number>
B; presence of a long ventral apophysis on trochanter, presence of a dorsal apophysis on femur, different shape of procursus, and short, hooked bulbal apophysis) and female genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1628,1651]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Belisana tauricornis Thorell, 1898, based on male (B, D) and female (A, C) syntypes. A. Epigynum, ventral view; B. Bulb, prolateral view; C. Vulva, dorsal view; D. Chelicerae, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216179/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
Figs 
<number box="[151,165,605,629]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A, C; different shape of epigynum in ventral view, different position of epigynal pockets, and long, bent pore plates).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,424,1242]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,582,677,702]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
Redescription. 
<collectingCountry box="[388,449,677,701]" name="Malta" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">Male</collectingCountry>
(
<typeStatus box="[471,569,677,702]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">syntype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 
<number box="[752,801,677,701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.66">1.66</number>
(
<number box="[823,873,677,701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.72">1.72</number>
with clypeus), prosoma 
<number box="[1177,1226,677,701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.57">0.57</number>
long, 
<number box="[1311,1360,677,701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.61">0.61</number>
wide, opisthosoma 
<number box="[299,348,713,737]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.09">1.09</number>
long, 
<number box="[419,468,713,737]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.58">0.58</number>
wide. Femur I: 
<number box="[649,698,713,737]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="3.5">3.50</number>
(other segments lost), leg III: – (
<number box="[1069,1119,713,737]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.56">1.56</number>
+ 
<number box="[1150,1199,713,737]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.2">0.20</number>
+ 
<number box="[1229,1278,713,737]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.31">1.31</number>
+ – + –), legs II and IV lost. Dorsal shield of prosoma brownish; ocular area yellowish; clypeus yellowish, with two paratactic, horn-shaped apophysis; sternum grey. Opisthosoma pale, without spots. Distance PME-PME 
<number box="[1208,1260,785,809]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.13">0.13</number>
; diameter PME 
<number box="[151,203,821,845]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.07">0.07</number>
; distance PME-ALE 
<number box="[453,505,821,845]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.01">0.01</number>
. Ocular area not elevated. No thoracic furrow. Sternum as long as wide (
<number box="[1369,1424,821,845]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.45">0.45</number>
). Chelicerae as in 
<figureCitation box="[345,414,857,881]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1628,1651]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Belisana tauricornis Thorell, 1898, based on male (B, D) and female (A, C) syntypes. A. Epigynum, ventral view; B. Bulb, prolateral view; C. Vulva, dorsal view; D. Chelicerae, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216179/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
Fig. 
<number box="[399,414,857,881]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D, with pair of thumb-shaped apophyses proximally, and pair of long, curved apophyses distally (distance between tips: 
<number box="[502,555,893,917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.43">0.43</number>
). Pedipalpi as in 
<figureCitation box="[745,810,893,917]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[199,1384,195,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[199,1386,195,1940]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Belisana tauricornis Thorell, 1898, based on male syntype. A – B. Pedipalpus (A, prolateral view; B, retrolateral view); C – D. Distal part of procursus (C, prolateral view; D, retrolateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216178/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
Figs 
<number box="[800,810,893,917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B; trochanter with a long ventral apophysis provided with a thumb-shaped apophysis retrolaterally; femur with a dorsal apophysis retrolaterally; procursus simple proximally but complex distally, with a retrolatero-dorsal membranous flap; bulb with a simple embolus and a short, hooked apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[437,506,1001,1025]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1628,1651]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Belisana tauricornis Thorell, 1898, based on male (B, D) and female (A, C) syntypes. A. Epigynum, ventral view; B. Bulb, prolateral view; C. Vulva, dorsal view; D. Chelicerae, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216179/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
Fig. 
<number box="[490,506,1001,1025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="303" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,424,1242]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,415,1037,1062]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
Female (
<typeStatus box="[303,402,1037,1062]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">syntype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Similar to male. One of the specimens measured as: Total length 
<number box="[1155,1204,1037,1061]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.5">1.50</number>
(
<number box="[1219,1269,1037,1061]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.61">1.61</number>
with clypeus), prosoma 
<number box="[256,305,1073,1097]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.56">0.56</number>
long, 
<number box="[379,428,1073,1097]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.59">0.59</number>
wide, opisthosoma 
<number box="[658,707,1073,1097]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.94">0.94</number>
long, 
<number box="[782,831,1073,1097]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.55">0.55</number>
wide. Legs I and II lost, leg III: 
<number box="[1212,1261,1073,1097]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="4.99">4.99</number>
(
<number box="[1278,1328,1073,1097]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.45">1.45</number>
+ 
<number box="[1362,1411,1073,1097]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.2">0.20</number>
+ 
<number box="[151,200,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.19">1.19</number>
+ 
<number box="[229,278,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.64">1.64</number>
+ 
<number box="[307,360,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.51">0.51</number>
), leg IV: 
<number box="[462,511,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="7.36">7.36</number>
(
<number box="[525,576,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="2.19">2.19</number>
+ 
<number box="[605,654,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.23">0.23</number>
+ 
<number box="[683,732,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="1.91">1.91</number>
+ 
<number box="[761,810,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="2.44">2.44</number>
+ 
<number box="[839,893,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.59">0.59</number>
). Distance PME-PME 
<number box="[1147,1199,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.13">0.13</number>
; diameter PME 
<number box="[1379,1431,1109,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.07">0.07</number>
; distance PME-ALE 
<number box="[381,433,1145,1169]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="0.01">0.01</number>
. Clypeus unmodified. Epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[824,892,1145,1169]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1628,1651]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Belisana tauricornis Thorell, 1898, based on male (B, D) and female (A, C) syntypes. A. Epigynum, ventral view; B. Bulb, prolateral view; C. Vulva, dorsal view; D. Chelicerae, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216179/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
Fig. 
<number box="[878,892,1145,1169]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A) simple and flat externally, with dark internal shade and pair of pockets. Vulva (
<figureCitation box="[532,598,1181,1205]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1628,1651]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Belisana tauricornis Thorell, 1898, based on male (B, D) and female (A, C) syntypes. A. Epigynum, ventral view; B. Bulb, prolateral view; C. Vulva, dorsal view; D. Chelicerae, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216179/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="303">
Fig. 
<number box="[584,598,1181,1205]" pageId="1" pageNumber="303" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C) with a wavy, sclerotized arch anteriorly and two long, bent pore plates.
</paragraph>
